<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-9F86EFE8-588D-4B84-A174-4CA4038D6670" version="5" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-9F86EFE8-588D-4B84-A174-4CA4038D6670" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Install the HTML TSM from a USB key</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Tools</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context id="CONTEXT_8EF3B1F09A6045C1B74B709625644461" class="- topic/section task/context "><p class="- topic/p ">This document describes how to install a more recent HTML TSM from USB key when it is not possible to update the TSM through Remote Service (disabled) 
</p></context><prereq id="PREREQ_018D2C0152F34CF4BABB47B5BABD53AE" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ul id="UL_D60F589B6D7943B2AA7A9EB8E40E533F" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_49A70D7FE3524F928A4F9263CC6D798F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A valid exported encrypted TSM must have been copied to a SAM key with sufficient internal memory or another USB key. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> (See 
<xref keyref="HTMLRobin002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-5C27F974-AF2D-473F-84EB-591CA36A3CBB.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to create an export of the TSM (in Robin)?>How to create an export of the TSM (in Robin)</xref>) 
</p></li><li id="LI_388EADC327474D0D82512223E1021946" class="- topic/li "><note id="GUID-803607B0-49C8-4E24-8AE9-D82F16EE606C" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> The SAM key or the USB key label must be: ROBINIMPORT 
</p></note></li></ul></prereq><steps id="GUID-A658A112-D7C8-4E1B-9920-99DFF69E2CD1" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> If the TSM is on the SAM key, plug-in the SAM key to the USB port of the printer. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">If the TSM is on a separate USB key you need to connect both SAM key and USB key with a splitter to the USB port of the printer. 
</p></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Start <ph varid="Adam" translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">ADAM</ph> 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="Start_adam" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-685E6504-D43E-4063-96D4-B0A4F752A1F6.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to start ADAM?>How to start ADAM</xref> 
</p></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap the TSM button in the <ph varid="Adam" translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">ADAM</ph> screen. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">Select the [Tools] icon (gear icon). 
</p><fig id="GUID-E0E6283F-AC3F-4976-9C6C-6C124FBEAF16" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-345583BA-2587-477E-A1A2-D01EF5811F44-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-345583BA-2587-477E-A1A2-D01EF5811F44-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Select [Import]. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-11588A26-2367-4B4F-831D-C9EAA6C5EF9C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-275F01CB-6FD3-4621-8EA0-72A850A7381C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-275F01CB-6FD3-4621-8EA0-72A850A7381C-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> You’ll see the internal TSM and the TSM (newer) on the USB key 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-57B58533-AC45-4F1F-B658-8A1DE3F049C9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0783BEE5-0790-486D-947A-94A2ECC32893-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0783BEE5-0790-486D-947A-94A2ECC32893-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Activate the [Import] of the Import container (Shift from red to green). 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="GUID-B2732D93-05B4-4080-B789-24DE053CE3B2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7C78773E-3B03-4F85-A14C-107B4CAF009C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7C78773E-3B03-4F85-A14C-107B4CAF009C-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Select [Apply]. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">The TSM is copied and installed on the controller. 
</p></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> After the TSM is copied completely, select Porthos to view the TSM. 
</cmd></step></steps></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-4998CEE3-DF0A-4501-ADA0-694495243747.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>HTML TSM on the Printer</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>